  "texts": [
    "Moreover, while LSTMs remain efficient, Transformers become increasingly computeintensive when generating progressively longer SMILES strings, which might limit their broad applicability in the chemical sciences.",
    "These aspects make it necessary to stretch the boundaries of current CLM approaches further, to chart the chemical space more effectively in search for bioactive molecules 25.",
    "Structured state space sequence models (S4s) are a recent member of the fast-growing family of state space architectures [33] [34] [35] [36], which are gathering increasing attention in the deep learning community [37] [38] [39] [40].",
    "S4s showed outstanding performance in audio, image, and text generation 35 and have a \"dual nature\": they (1) are trained over the entire input sequences to learn complex global properties and (2) generate one string element at a timethereby combining some respective strengths of Transformers and LSTMs.",
    "Motivated by such \"best of two worlds\" behavior, here we ask the following question: Can S4 advance the current state-of-the-art in chemical language modeling?"
  ],
